          "End of Course",
          "Authors “normalized” course duration as 270 days. \n\nThe presented model receives a dataset containing multiple multi-variate time series (each timeseries consists of a student in a course module edition). This dataset is passed through 3-layer LSTM, whose output is passed to a Dropout layer (into an attention layer).\n\nThe embedding resulting from the Attention module is the input to the “final” MLP. ",
          "RF, Naive Bayes, MLP, SEPN, MTAPSP",
          "Holdout Method",
          "Macro:\n{Precision: 0.69 - MTAPSP, Recall: 0.66 - MTAPSP, F1-Score: 0.67 - MTAPSP, Accuracy: 0.74 - MTAPSP}\n\nWeighted:\n{Precision: 0.73 - MTAPSP, Recall: 0.74 - MTAPSP, F1-Score: 0.73 - MTAPSP}",
          "The authors’ work is done in multiple stages: \n\n1. One experiment evaluating class specific metrics and no early prediction comparing multiple “candidate algorithms” - MTAPSP wings on all acounts. \n\n\n",
          "- Reports mentioned in Abstract are misleading - they refer to Wi-FD on 100% course duration.\n\n- Holdout method\n\n- Only tested in OULAD\n"
        ],
        [
          "Classification",
          "Higher Education",
          "E-Learning",
          "End of Course Performance",
          "Pass (1) vs Fail (0)",
          "32593 OULAD students",
