          "20%, 40%, 60%, 80%  and 100% course duration",
          "Authors “normalized” course duration as 270 days. \n\nThe presented model receives a dataset containing multiple multi-variate time series (each timeseries consists of a student in a course module edition). This dataset is passed through 3-layer LSTM, whose output is passed to a Dropout layer (into an attention layer).\n\nThe embedding resulting from the Attention module is the input to the “final” MLP. v",
          "TEnc, MTAPSP",
          "Holdout Method",
          "20%\n{Accuracy: 0.9573 - MTAPSP - W-PD (daily), F1-Score: 0.9571 - MTAPSP - W-PD (daily)}\n\n40%\n{Accuracy: 0.961 - MTAPSP - W-PD (weekly), F1-Score: 0.9608 - MTAPSP - W-PD (weekly)}\n\n60%\n{Accuracy: 0.9728 - MTAPSP - W-PD (daily), F1-Score: 0.9727 - MTAPSP - W-PD (daily)}\n\n80%\n{Accuracy: 0.9808 - MTAPSP - W-PD (daily), F1-Score: 0.9808 - MTAPSP - W-PD (daily)}\n\n100%\n{Accuracy: 0.9908 - MTAPSP - W-PD (daily), F1-Score: 0.9908 - MTAPSP - W-PD (daily)}\n",
          "2. Authors do different forms of classification at different stages of course completion:\n\nWF-PD: Pass-Fail\nF-PD: Pass vs Fail (excluding dropouts)\nW-PD: Dropout vs Pass\n\n3. Ablation studies to see effects of the different layers in the overall predictive process.\n \n2. forms of representation are considered: Daily and Weekly,",
